Medics take the temperature of a patient waiting for treatment at the Wuhan Union Hospital Waiting Area on March 18,2010. Caijing reporter Xinna / photography

Wen | CAIJING special correspondent Wuhan, Xinna, intern reporter, Zhu He

Editor | Wang Xiao

The good news is that the doors opened on March 19,2020: As of 2400 on March 18, there were zero new confirmed cases in Hubei and Wuhan, and zero new or existing suspected cases in Wuhan.

Five days earlier, Wuhan had been zero additional confirmed cases for a time. From March 13 to March 17, a total of 14 new cases were confirmed in Wuhan, including 6 out-patients. Although the absolute number of cases from outpatient clinics is small, it is still regarded by experts as a red flag that must be strictly controlled.

On March 18, the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission reported the only confirmed case, also from an outpatient clinic. This has aroused great attention of medical experts and institutions at all levels.

While fully affirming the achievements of China's epidemic prevention and control work, we must clearly see the complexity and severity of the epidemic situation at home and abroad, General Secretary of the Communist Party of China said in an important speech at the Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China on March 18. The tasks of medical treatment, community prevention and control and follow-up in Hubei and Wuhan are still arduous, and the risk of a resurgence of the epidemic remains due to the increased mobility and concentration of people in other areas.

According to the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission, the newly diagnosed patient on March 18 had left for an overnight shift at sister-in-law's tree farm in Kong Hon district at 5 p.m. on February 24. He returned to his home in the morning of February 25. No one was contacted. The source of infection of this patient may be the market or the market exposure caused by exposure to infection. Sister-in-law tree vegetable market from the south China Seafood Market Walk less than 3 km.

"CAIJING" reporter learned that Wuhan has 43 hospitals have gradually opened general outpatient service, general outpatient service testing are starting normal charges. Recently, there are outsiders to the third-class Hospital in Wuhan, from the probability point of view, this has also increased the potential risk of multiple infections.

According to medical experts, the danger of finding cases in outpatient clinics is that these newly diagnosed patients may be the source of infection missed in the city-wide screening, which increases the likelihood of a resurgence of the epidemic.

However, Professor Chen Kun of the public health at the Zhejiang University told Caijing that the emergence of new cases of community-acquired pneumonia was also a "normal" pattern in the epidemic. What is important is to do a good epidemiological investigation, early detection, early isolation, and through the now effective quarantine, epidemic prevention measures, epidemic points will be culled.

Returning to work may increase the risk of infection

Fourteen new cases were confirmed within five days, of which six were out-patients. This is not good news for Wang Mu (not his real name) , who keeps a daily tally of new cases of pneumonia in Wuhan. It was her 53rd day in Wuhan and her 30th day in the community. Her question is, where do these clinic confirmed patients come from?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
An isolated observation point in Wuhan was fully disinfected three times a day. Caijing reporter, Wang Xiao/ photography

Wuhan Health Commission on March 18,2020, March 17,00-24 hours, Wuhan, an additional confirmed case from the outpatient clinic. The patient lives in Golden Graceland, Hon Hing Street, Kong Hon district, and works as a vegetable market manager for his sister-in-law.

"CAIJING" reporters obtained a notice, a detailed record of the patient's situation, the notice from his neighborhood committee.

On the evening of March 15, the patient presented with a cough accompanied by chest tightness and no fever. After contacting the doctor, the patient was arranged to go to Wuhan Integrated Hospital of Traditional Chinese and Western medicine (also known as Xinhua Hospital) for medical treatment in the morning of March 16, accompanied by a community worker, the results of the same day did not show the characteristics of new pneumonia, NUCLEIC ACID test results were not out. The patient was released from the hospital and has not left his home since.

On the evening of March 17, the community received oral feedback from superiors that the patient tested positive for nucleic acid. The patient was taken out of the community overnight and is now hospitalized in a downtown hospital. Two family members have been taken to a quarantined hotel for close contacts. At present, the above-mentioned family members in good physical condition, no fever, no chest tightness, shortness of breath and other symptoms.

Epidemiological investigations revealed that the confirmed patient had no fever at all times and had only a mild cough. In February and March, I went to the East Gate of Jinya Phase III to pick up the daily necessities sent by my friends. His wife had taken supplies three times and had no direct contact with others.

At 5 pm on February 24, the confirmed patient went out to sister-in-law's tree vegetable farm for a night shift, and returned home in the morning of February 25, no contact.

March 18, the above-mentioned Wuhan City Health Commission Report described the source of infection is presumed to be exposed to the market or market personnel caused by infection.

Another additional patient with a history of working outside the home was diagnosed on March 15. According to the Wuhan Health Commission reported that the patient lived in Wuchang District Bairuijing 2, had been in the community activities, work and hospital experience.

On March 18, a staff member of his community introduced Caijing, and two days before that, the resident began to resume work. Their Unit for the staff to do physical examination, and then in Wuhan Tianyou hospital to do a nucleic acid test, the results were positive. After the diagnosis, the patient has been the first time to be sent to the Guanggu area of a designated hospital isolation treatment.

At present, the floor where he lives has been eliminated, and close contacts who live at home have entered the isolation point for medical observation. "In addition to him, there is one person in the family who works on the street, and two people go out to work every day, " said the staff member, who said it was difficult to find out exactly where the infection came from.

"We can not rule out the possibility of community or family members being infected, " the Wuhan Health and Health Commission said, explaining the possible cause of the patient's infection.

Out-patient nucleic acid test and so on all need to pay for oneself

"We don't know what's going on, " said a Wuhan Union Hospital medical worker after learning that the new cases were coming from outpatient clinics. The Wuhan Union Hospital was among the first to open. As of this week, the doors of the long-closed clinic in its home district have reopened.

Starting from mid-march, some hospitals in Wuhan have gradually resumed their general outpatient clinics and opened wards for non-new crown pneumonia patients. The daily list of non-new Crown designated hospitals and the opening of outpatient, emergency and inpatient departments can be found on the official website of Wuhan Health Commission.

As at 12:00 on 17 March, 35 non-new Crown Sentinel medical institutions had treated only non-new crown patients and 8 new crown and non-new crown patients, and these 43 institutions had resumed part of their outpatient and inpatient departments.

At 3 p.m. on March 18, in the Waiting Area for cardiac surgery on the second floor of the Wuhan Union Hospital, a Caijing reporter met a young woman with a colorful hat and a 21 day old baby in her arms. They drove themselves from a county near Wuhan. They can enter Wuhan at this time is not easy, need to prepare a number of materials: County Hospital referral form, health card, etc. .

The woman told the "CAIJING" reporter, the child was born shortly after the symptoms of Hypoxia, county hospital conditions are limited, can not be diagnosed, "these two days more and more serious symptoms, crying, especially obvious, out of breath. They had previously consulted with Concorde's heart surgeon via an online consultation and the initial results were "congenital heart defect" .

They came as soon as they heard that the Wuhan Union Hospital was opening. "If the child wasn't sick, we wouldn't have risked going to Wuhan, " said the mother, who said the child was still young and wanted treatment as soon as possible.

They were confronted by heavily armed medical personnel, wearing protective clothing, eyes, face masks and face masks, much like the doctors in the fever clinic. As long as two or three people around, they will open their arms, "back, back, do not encircle. ". This corresponds to the ubiquitous "keep your distance from others, at least 1 meter or more" notice in the clinic building.

"CAIJING" reporter saw that the hospital has made detailed records, each patient has been fully registered name, age, medical card information. The card is tied to the home address and phone number in the window.

After filling out the information, the thermometer is held up to the forehead. If the body temperature exceeds 37.3 °c, the temperature gun will automatically alarm. According to a staff member at the guide desk, patients with fever will be isolated immediately and sent to the designated hospital. In addition to taking body temperature, the patient's Oxygenation is also checked with a Oxygenation. The patient also needs to answer whether he or she has had contact with a patient who has been diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia.

If admitted to the hospital, the first test to rule out the new coronary pneumonia, to be admitted to hospital. The above-mentioned medical personnel, not only to do CT, two nucleic acid testing, but also to do serum antibody testing.

"CAIJING" reporter learned that the above-mentioned detection items are required at their own expense, of which 300 yuan nucleic acid detection, serum antibody more than 100 yuan.

Most hospitals in Wuhan are turning their attention to open general outpatient clinics and wards. A third-class hospital, said the deputy director of the recent main focus on outpatient services, the situation has improved significantly.

Still need to guard against the risk of resuming work

Wuhan recently added from the Outpatient Department of some confirmed patients, suggesting that some communities also have new pneumonia patients. However, Guo Xiuhua, deputy director of the Public Health at the Capital University of Medical Sciences, said that individual confirmed cases were rare events. The general trend is that the epidemic has been brought under control and normal economic activities can be carried out.

Earlier, Ning Yi, a professor at Peking University's Public Health, told CAIJING that the overall trend is declining rapidly, and local outbreaks can never be ruled out. If you can't control it, it's a fire. Be On your guard. There'll be fewer and fewer sparks.

Will the newly confirmed cases associated with work travel cause a resurgence of the epidemic in some areas?

Chen Kun, a professor at the Public Health at the Zhejiang University, said that measures to prevent and control infectious diseases should be adapted to local conditions and circumstances, and strategies and measures should be adjusted according to the changing situation, it is also the same reason that the classification, division, division and time interval are being carried out.

On March 18, Cao Guangjing, vice governor of the Government of the People's Republic of China of Hubei Province, said at a press conference on the epidemic prevention and control work that Wuhan's first-class enterprises could continue to resume work and production, other enterprises shall arrange to resume work and production no earlier than March 20 at 2400 hours. According to the interpretation of government departments, the first category of enterprises refers to the protection of epidemic prevention and control, the People's Daily necessities and other enterprises.

Hu Shanlian, a professor at the public health at the Fudan University, suggested that the resuming work unit should take full responsibility and pay special attention to the organization. From the technical measures, you can slowly let go, on the staff's working hours, dining time in the canteen for the dislocation arrangements, play a time difference, do not gather together.

He also suggested that individuals should pay more attention to health protection, wear masks, wash hands frequently, maintain social distance, ventilation, do not go to crowded places.

As for when the city will be able to lift its closure and resume normal work and life, Chinese Academy of Engineering Academician Li Lanjuan told the media that the number of new confirmed cases in Wuhan is expected to be Zero by March 20. If there are no more confirmed cases, the problem of "closing the city" in Wuhan can be solved and normal work and production life can be resumed.

According to the above-mentioned Projections, Wuhan is expected to consider in early April to resolve the "closure" issue. But up to now, Hubei and Wuhan have not yet authority authority body face-to-face talk about the specific timetable for the city to lift the blockade.
